Python Project Structure:
  .env - a text file used for environment variables
       - keeps secrets/config out of your code
       - typically uses the dotenv package to access keys inside
  .gitignore - prevents certain files/folders from being committed to github
             - typically python cache's, models, virtual environments
  my_package - holds modules u can use in other parts of your project
  _init_.py - initializer for grouping multiple modules together

in Python EVERYTHING IS AN OBJECT
  objects = data + behaviour
  objects have attributes (data stored inside) and methods (functions that belong to the object)

